headline: Henry Schein (HSIC) Valuation: Taking Stock After Q2 Earnings Miss and Weaker U.S. Dental Demand
summary: If you follow Henry Schein (HSIC), you likely noticed the recent dip after its Q2 earnings report was released. The company missed profit expectations this time around, with executives pointing to softer demand in the U.S. dental business as a key drag. High interest rates, persistent inflation, and more cautious patient behavior toward non-urgent dental procedures all appeared to affect the latest results. These factors have put investors on alert regarding how persistent these pressures...

headline: 2 Safe-and-Steady Stocks to Target This Week and 1 Facing Headwinds
summary: A stock with low volatility can be reassuring, but it doesn’t always mean strong long-term performance. Investors who prioritize stability may miss out on higher-reward opportunities elsewhere.
